"But machines sometimes are specious things to amuse the reader, and give a colour of probability to things otherwise incredible. And, besides, it soothed the vanity of the Romans, to find the gods 8o visibly concerned in all the actions of their pre- decessors. We, who are better taught by our re= ligion, yet own every wonderful accident, which befals us for the best, to be brought to pass by some special providence of Almighty God, and by the care of guardian angels : and from hence I might infer, that no heroic poem can be writ on the Epis"